Parliament, Thursday, 7 March 2019 – A joint meeting of the Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will tomorrow conduct public hearings on the 2019 Division of Revenue Bill, which provides for the equitable allocation of revenue for the national, provincial and local spheres of government. The committees are also expected to receive input from the Financial and Fiscal Commission (FFC) and the South African Local Government Association (Salga). Details of the hearings are as follows: Date: Friday, 8 March 2019
	Time: 9 am 
	Venue: Committee Room E249, Second Floor, National Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA AND MR CHAREL DE BEER. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
	E-mail: flombard@parliament.gov.za Democracy is not an event that occurred in 1994. It is a process to which all of us can contribute by making our voices heard in Parliament, in the provincial legislatures and in broader society.Read more